cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new framework for imitation learning algorithm that actively and interactively learns a model of the user's reward function with efficient queries. It also uses adversarial neural networks and successor feature models, which are common techniques in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with aligning agent policy with human expert behavior in a reinforcement learning setting, which is a common problem in AI. 

Furthermore, it may belong to cs.RO (Robotics) as it evaluates the proposed method on robotic control tasks. 

It may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it evaluates the proposed method on image-based video games, which involve high-dimensional observation and complex state dynamics. 

Finally, it may belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with learning to avoid unsafe states when training the reward model, which is a common problem in control systems.
